From 01cc8c0563fac74c56aa3883b19d92ee3ed862d1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ho Cheung <hocheung@chromium.org>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 04:54:23 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [Linux] Fix deb dependency generation with vendored dpkg
 modules

Fix Linux deb dependency generation by vendoring the minimal dpkg perl
module set and dpkg architecture data that match Chromium's vendored
dpkg-shlibdeps.pl baseline.

Also point calculate_package_deps.py at the vendored modules via
PERL5LIB and DPKG_DATADIR so packaging no longer depends on the host
libdpkg-perl installation.

Keep the local --ignore-weak-undefined patch and drop the old
compatibility patch, which is no longer needed once the matching
modules are vendored.

Bug: 483655379
Change-Id: I8916ae3bbc216aad18e77337da1e3bdc373f04cb
Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/7725703
Reviewed-by: Lei Zhang <thestig@chromium.org>
Commit-Queue: Aaron Teo <hocheung@chromium.org>
Cr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/main@{#1610669}
